  "prompt": "What are the must watch Hollywood movies before you die (count not more than 10)?",
  "response": "Determining a list of must-watch Hollywood movies can be quite subjective, as it often depends on personal taste and preferences. However, here is a diverse selection of ten widely acclaimed films that are frequently recommended by critics and audiences alike:\n\n1. **\"The Godfather\" (1972)** - Directed by Francis Ford Coppola, this classic crime drama offers a deep dive into a powerful Italian-American crime family and features iconic performances by Marlon Brando and Al Pacino.\n\n2. **\"Casablanca\" (1942)** - A timeless romance set against the backdrop of World War II, directed by Michael Curtiz and starring Humphrey Bogart and Ingrid Bergman.\n\n3. **\"Schindler's List\" (1993)** - Steven Spielberg\u2019s harrowing portrayal of the Holocaust, focusing on Oskar Schindler, who saved over a thousand Polish-Jewish refugees during the war.\n\n4. **\"Pulp Fiction\" (1994)** - Quentin Tarantino\u2019s seminal film weaves multiple interconnected stories with sharp dialogue and a non-linear narrative style, featuring John Travolta, Uma Thurman, and Samuel L. Jackson.\n\n5. **\"The Shawshank Redemption\" (1994)** - Directed by Frank Darabont, this inspirational tale of hope and friendship in a brutal prison setting stars Tim Robbins and Morgan Freeman.\n\n6. **\"Citizen Kane\" (1941)** - Orson Welles\u2019 groundbreaking film about the rise and fall of a media tycoon is often lauded for its innovative narrative structure and cinematography.\n\n7. **\"Star Wars: Episode IV - A New Hope\" (1977)** - George Lucas\u2019 epic space opera launched a cultural phenomenon and reshaped the science fiction genre.\n\n8. **\"The Dark Knight\" (2008)** - Christopher Nolan\u2019s critically acclaimed superhero film, with a legendary performance by Heath Ledger as the Joker, explores themes of chaos and justice.\n\n9. **\"Gone with the Wind\" (1939)** - This epic romance set during the American Civil War, directed by Victor Fleming, remains a cinematic classic with standout performances from Vivien Leigh and Clark Gable.\n\n10. **\"Forrest Gump\" (1994)** - Directed by Robert Zemeckis, this heartwarming film follows the extraordinary life of Forrest Gump, played by Tom Hanks, as he inadvertently influences several historical events.\n\nThese selections represent a mix of different genres and eras, providing a wide-ranging look at Hollywood\u2019s storytelling and filmmaking capabilities.",
